sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1897025
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The construct contains a high expression promoter J23100 with a strong RBS (BBa_B0034) in a cassette (BBa_K314100), followed by a CDS of ALR (BBa_K1172901) and a lambda t0 terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Keshiniy Madivannan

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K314100
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: High constitutive protein expression insert includes f1 origin and RBS B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tomas Huber, Justin Siegel

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1172901
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Alanine-racemase extracted from genomic DNA from E. coli KRX. Used for our biosafety project.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Tore Bleckwehl
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Ligation via Gibson-assembly, so the primer had to have certain extensions
